But like, I don't know, like, were you always a believer in like conservative politics?

200
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:50,460
Or was it more just like, oh, I'm like getting all these access and opportunities.

201
00:16:50,460 --> 00:16:52,400
And suddenly you're like finding yourself in it.

202
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:58,100
I think there were parts of it that were appealing, because when I first went to college, I went for philosophy.

203
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:03,140
And to me, philosophy, you're supposed to be open minded and consider both sides of the argument.

204
00:17:03,319 --> 00:17:14,940
And right as I'm a freshman in college, Donald Trump was going to visit the school and every head of the philosophy department signed a petition to stop him from speaking there.

205
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:16,859
And I was like, whoa, hang on.

206
00:17:16,940 --> 00:17:23,460
You know, I disagree with some of the things this guy says, but isn't that really like antithetical to what we're supposed to be doing there?

207
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:33,140
And so I think some of that really vitriolic backlash, which now there's a point to be said, like maybe maybe they saw things we didn't see before.

208
00:17:33,220 --> 00:17:39,240
But in that moment, it's like it was so intense that it almost causes the inverse reaction.

209
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:42,320
And I didn't experience life.

210
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:46,460
I'm sitting here debating socialism and whether or not people should have health care.

211
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,140
And I was on my dad's plan.

212
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:54,860
So it was just like, you know, I'm sitting here telling people like, oh, you know, don't get handouts and work for your own.

213
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:56,180
And I'm on my dad's health care.

214
00:17:56,580 --> 00:18:00,160
And so it was also just like the ignorance of youth.

215
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:06,940
And again, it was one of the first eras because I don't really count the Obama era as like an influencer era.

216
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:08,000
It really was Trump.

217
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:21,080
And that's the first time ever that you were able to get this validation and feel like you were right, even if you were wrong, because it was blowing up online or you got a lot of likes.

218
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:24,080
And you don't know why people are liking things.

219
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:27,360
You don't know if it's because it's it pushes their agenda or whatever.

220
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:34,920
And so there were all these crazy factors that when you're a young hungry kid is really attractive.

221
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:35,780
Totally.

222
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:41,880
I mean, I think I was talking to somebody that went through like the Daily Callers, like news journalism program or whatever.

223
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:47,020
And there's so many journalists I know in media that have gone through these like sort of right wing pipelines.

224
00:18:47,020 --> 00:18:51,580
And it's because they exist, like they're well funded and there's opportunities.

225
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:54,060
And I totally understand being a young person.

226
00:18:54,060 --> 00:18:56,800
I mean, I was talking to a kid that worked for a kid.

227
00:18:56,860 --> 00:18:58,640
He was like 22, but like worked for Doge.

228
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:00,260
And I'm like, why the hell would you work for Doge?

229
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:01,560
And he's like, I don't know.

230
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:02,360
I'm an engineer.

231
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:05,000
And like, it's cool to work for the government and have that on my resume.

232
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:12,020
Like when you're young and ambitious, I think like you end up accepting opportunities without maybe like thinking that hard about it.

233
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:19,560
And so I can totally see, especially during that era when like especially you were a young woman and they were so after like young women.

234
00:19:19,780 --> 00:19:20,320
You know what I mean?

235
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:20,720
Yeah.

236
00:19:20,820 --> 00:19:30,600
And what people I also so I was homeschooled in high school, which gave me a lot more social skills than some people who were homeschooled a bit longer.

237
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:36,940
But there was also I just wanted the friend group I didn't have in high school, so to speak.

238
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:42,080
And so there was very much like a yearning for some sort of community or belonging to.

239
00:19:42,180 --> 00:19:44,180
And I'm like, oh, my God, they like me.

240
00:19:44,860 --> 00:19:52,000
And that's you know, and I felt the same way when I got invited to a party when I first started college or whatever.

241
00:19:52,160 --> 00:20:07,420
So I think that was also very appealing in a way that kind of makes you ignore other ideologies or flaws in certain thinking or why I didn't critically think about the issue of health care.

242
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:08,100
Yeah.

243
00:20:08,220 --> 00:20:14,620
Well, also, it's like when you take a hard position or especially during that era of MAGA before, like, I know liberals were like Trump was always like this.

244
00:20:14,740 --> 00:20:14,940
Yes.

245
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:16,940
But like it was a different it was different.

246
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:23,820
Trump 1.0 was radically different than sort of Trump 2.0. But that is very important, though, because it was not what it is now.

247
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:34,060
And maybe they were more suppressed, but it was a lot easier to a lot of the isms were much better disguised in 2016.

248
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:38,940
I would argue that as somebody that covered Trump, that was a fascist, in my opinion.

249
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:40,900
And by the way, I consider the Democrats fascist, too.

250
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:44,600
Just to be clear, I hate like so much about our political system generally.

251
00:20:44,780 --> 00:20:45,900
I think the tendencies were there.

252
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:46,920
I think their goals were there.

253
00:20:46,940 --> 00:20:50,900
But I do think that there was this like at least plausible deniability or not plausible.

254
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:56,100
But there was this thing that I would speak to so many Trump voters back then that were like, no, you're wrong.

255
00:20:56,340 --> 00:20:56,800
You're wrong.

256
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,240
I don't believe that he would do this.

257
00:20:58,320 --> 00:21:00,960
I don't believe that this would happen even now today.

258
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,540
Like a lot of them are like, no, no, no.

259
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:06,300
You know, so I do think that there's a level of like, was this always the end goal?

260
00:21:06,380 --> 00:21:11,660
Like, I mean, he did run on a campaign of mass deportation in 2016.

261
00:21:11,780 --> 00:21:12,960
But like, I don't know.

262
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:17,740
I am sympathetic in the sense that I've seen a lot of people evolve in the way that you're talking about.

263
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:26,300
I also think that like when you are in the MAGA movement, there are these insufferable liberals that are terrible and are abusive and also counterproductive.

264
00:21:26,420 --> 00:21:34,300
I mean, I'm thinking of like the Jasmine Crockett discourse, I guess, where they're like, you can't criticize a black woman or something like weaponizing identity in this way that like I am sympathetic.

265
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:34,860
Yeah.

266
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:38,600
And calling people who are very obviously not racist, racist.

267
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:44,200
And, you know, that was a big turnoff when you're first forming a political ideology.

268
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:59,780
But I think it's also important to understand how much because I watch this as someone who was always public facing in a way and always speaking out publicly, the restraints on what you could say without backlash became stricter and stricter.

269
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:00,080
Right.

270
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:09,600
Like if you look at the photo of Trump with the LGBTQ flag like years ago, if that photo came out now, he would not be president at all.

271
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:13,360
There would be such immense backlash from the base.

272
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:19,000
And so the Overton window has certainly shifted for the Republicans.

273
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:19,940
Yeah.

274
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:30,000
I mean, I do think that like people would say like maybe you were you as in like the MAGA supporters were part of shifting that Overton window, though.

275
00:22:30,180 --> 00:22:31,840
Like and I'm curious your thoughts.

276
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:36,020
Like I know you spoke out on Twitter recently about LGBTQ issues.

277
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:40,880
And, you know, you're known for writing this like anti-trans children's book.

278
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:50,480
And so I'm curious, like how your thoughts on LGBTQ rights and gender identity and stuff has evolved as well, because it seems like that's something that you've changed your mind on, too.

279
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:55,220
Yeah, because it's also again, I didn't live life as a real person.

280
00:22:55,220 --> 00:22:58,040
I was writing a children's book before I ever had children.

281
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:03,520
And, you know, like I did not have any children when I wrote the children's book.

282
00:23:03,660 --> 00:23:05,780
But it's also just experience.

283
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:19,400
And I felt a lot of guilt, especially now that it's closer to my family, the trans issue, that it's hard for me to think of causing someone who is part of my family to an extent any pain.

284
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:25,900
And sometimes you do have to have those personal experiences to really wake up and say, what are we doing?

285
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:27,440
Is this issue really important?

286
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:31,900
Are they just demonizing a group of people to obfuscate from real issues?

287
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:44,840
And the more I would hear about this, and if you look at my page, even though I did the anti-trans book back in whenever that was, 2021, I think, after that, there's a few comments on the trans issue.

288
00:23:44,940 --> 00:23:52,160
But as it picked up steam amongst the right wing, I didn't pick up steam with it because it very much seemed like a scapegoat.

289
00:23:52,160 --> 00:24:02,960
And I felt like I was watching a very, very small percentage of the population be used as a scapegoat and used as the guise of women's rights.

290
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:04,500
We care about women and girls.

291
00:24:05,100 --> 00:24:07,580
And it's the only time they would ever say this.

292
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:18,820
And meanwhile, I'm watching behind the scenes while very powerful people who are known within the MAGA movement and these conservative movements to be very abusive towards women.

293
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:23,100
They're allowed to stay because they just do good work or they don't take women seriously.

294
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:35,980
And so their own behavior and their own mismanagement of certain abuses within the movement also caused me to rethink, like, hey, are they just using a very small demographic of people as a scapegoat?

295
00:24:36,420 --> 00:24:47,780
And that to me, like even the Biden Trans Day of Visibility, I have a very public tweet because they were upset that Biden made a Trans Day of Visibility announcement, I think it was on Easter.

296
00:24:48,040 --> 00:24:53,320
And I said, guys, this has been on the same day for many years and they do it all the time.

297
00:24:53,440 --> 00:25:00,460
Anyone who's saying this is like an attack on America and like the transing of America, you're just, you're liars.

298
00:25:00,980 --> 00:25:04,520
And that was, I think, two years ago that I posted that.

299
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:13,560
The hardest part for me is just figuring out how to make amends and learn because there was just a lot that I also didn't know.

300
00:25:13,620 --> 00:25:14,440
I was very ignorant.

301
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:16,680
It's kind of like the health care situation.

302
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:25,060
I was, you know, saying nobody deserves health care and I'm on my dad's plan and I'm speaking about a demographic that I really don't know or understand.

303
00:25:26,020 --> 00:25:37,020
And it wasn't until it affected me personally, which I know is a cliche, that I was like, oh, I'm really causing pain now to people in my life.

304
00:25:37,020 --> 00:25:37,460
Right.

305
00:25:37,580 --> 00:25:51,180
Well, like for people that don't know your son with Elon, his sister, Vivian, is trans and very happily trans, like out proud, thriving in a way that I think makes Elon like incredibly angry or something.

306
00:25:51,620 --> 00:25:57,020
But I'm curious what other moments broke through for you on that issue.

307
00:25:57,120 --> 00:26:04,100
Like, you know, when you look back over that evolution over the past four or five years, like what were other moments or pieces of information?

308
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:12,980
There were certain companies that I worked for that I can't name, but they were very involved in the trans issue.

309
00:26:13,340 --> 00:26:20,640
And while there were certain things that were crazy, okay, there's a drag queen twerking at this bar or whatever, and that's absurd.

310
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:22,980
Those really seem like edge cases and outliers.

311
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:28,880
Even working with certain individuals, it just got really mean.

312
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:39,940
And it came from, oh, we're going to highlight really extreme cases to anyone who is trans, is mentally ill, and you know, we're going to dox them, we're going to put them out here.

313
00:26:40,060 --> 00:26:42,900
And it just didn't sit right with me.

314
00:26:43,080 --> 00:26:47,860
And I knew some of these people, like through being mutuals on Twitter, that were being attacked.

315
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:51,980
And like, they were always very kind and normal human beings.

316
00:26:52,360 --> 00:27:02,240
And I just, it really hurt me to see that being done and think about the way that I helped push that or normalize that as well.

317
00:27:02,540 --> 00:27:14,120
I saw in your tweet, you know, you were saying you were hesitant to weigh in on this because you don't want to seem like you're like, oh, they're going to say like, oh, you're just being opportunistic, or oh, you're just scorned, and now you're pivoting.

318
00:27:14,260 --> 00:27:29,380
And I feel like that happens a lot where, you know, I've talked to some other people on the right that I know have evolved on certain issues, and they don't want to speak out because they feel like it'll be seen where people will be like, oh, now you're just grifting because whatever they, you know, as if there's any place to grift on the left, by the way, there's no money on the left.

319
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:30,240
Surprise, surprise.

320
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:30,840
I know.

321
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,960
And I did that when I didn't have a checkmark.

322
00:27:34,020 --> 00:27:36,440
Okay, so I did not make any money on that.

323
00:27:36,540 --> 00:27:42,460
As soon as I lost my checkmark, I was like, well, might as well say everything that I don't want to be accused of grifting on.

324
00:27:42,900 --> 00:27:44,440
I'm not making money on this anyway.

325
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:46,760
So no, there's not.

326
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:53,800
And I just, I'm back in school, like I'm not trying to start the defectors of MAGA for democracy over here.

327
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:58,040
I'm trying to finish my degree and raise my kids.

328
00:27:58,240 --> 00:28:11,600
But I also recognize that because a lot of the turn was from my own personal experience, like I also have to recognize that that was incredibly unempathetic of me to only recognize it like directly impacted me.

329
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:17,780
And the best I can do now is, is ask people how I can help and how I can be a better advocate.

330
00:28:17,780 --> 00:28:22,320
Like, I'm not going to go out there and say, now I'm the trans activist who speaks for everyone.

331
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:27,360
But like, if there's anything I can do, I'm willing to listen and make amends for those things.

332
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:36,960
Well, so I think, I mean, now you have children too, and you can raise your children in a loving environment and accept them no matter how they turn out, you know, which I think matters.

333
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:39,160
I want them to be kind individuals.

334
00:28:39,620 --> 00:28:46,320
Like if they were ever saying some of the things that I've seen online, like I wouldn't know who they are.

335
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:53,980
You know, I would be so disappointed in myself if my children spoke the way that some of these people speak about these communities.

336
00:28:54,420 --> 00:29:01,380
And so I have to be a better example because I was quite mean and not understanding at all.

337
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:02,140
Yeah.

338
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:04,220
Well, it's like, it's so crazy too.

339
00:29:04,420 --> 00:29:13,460
I mean, the hypocrisy from the conservative movement as somebody that grew up around a lot of like old school Republicans, where it was very much like, get the government out of my life, maybe more libertarian.

340
00:29:13,860 --> 00:29:23,040
It seems like there's just this like aggressive effort to police other people and police other people's like gender expression and identity and like the way they want to live their lives.

341
00:29:23,100 --> 00:29:33,660
I just think like they deserve the personal liberties that we all deserve, which is the right to just like live their life in peace and do whatever they want, like wear whatever they want, change their name to whatever they want.

342
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:34,740
Like who cares?

343
00:29:35,020 --> 00:29:36,600
You know, they're not harming anyone.

344
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:43,640
It's also when they, when they frame it as some mental illness, this also insinuates that these people are well, who are seeing this.

345
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:51,820
And there's an incredible amount of delusion with many of these people on the right who are calling themselves men and are giant.

346
00:29:53,420 --> 00:29:56,920
So, you know, I think they need to get themselves together.

347
00:29:57,160 --> 00:30:02,420
I think they need to figure out who they are and do some introspection there.

348
00:30:02,740 --> 00:30:09,600
I feel like one of the biggest topics in sort of like Trump 2.0 or like one of the biggest issues right now is immigration.

349
00:30:10,440 --> 00:30:24,240
And I think a lot of people I've talked to a lot of Trump voters from Trump 1.0 that say that they regret voting from a second time now that they're seeing, you know, ICE in sort of like the brutality at which they're like deporting people.

350
00:30:24,340 --> 00:30:27,400
Nevermind, by the way, Joe Biden was happily funding ICE and Obama.

351
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:28,280
So whatever.

352
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:31,800
But, you know, I think both parties are complicit when it comes to the ICE stuff.

353
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:43,620
But have your views on any other issues like immigration change or like how has sort of evolving your perspective on LGBTQ rights, health care, et cetera, like are affected, like I guess, like the way you view these other issues.

354
00:30:44,320 --> 00:31:02,800
So I'll preface this too by saying a lot of change is not only from my personal experience, but I do think getting off the internet for a while was very helpful because it was the first time since I was 10 or 11 that I had been off the internet when I had this very public scandal and decided to take like a mental health hiatus for quite some time.

355
00:31:02,940 --> 00:31:07,820
So I was able to develop and really think about my own experiences on my own terms.

356
00:31:08,420 --> 00:31:19,280
And one of those was also immigration, because I did a lot of reporting at the border and I saw vast amounts of people coming in here who we did not know who they were.

357
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:30,380
And from my perspective, I was like, this is a massive national security issue to not know who's coming in here and to see burned IDs and passports and buried IDs at the border.

358
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:32,420
And we don't know where these children are.

359
00:31:32,540 --> 00:31:41,400
And at one point, I was arguing with Mark Cuban in direct messages about this issue when he was on his like Kamala spin and he was a bit of a lol cow.

360
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:44,780
And he was telling me, you know, Ashley, they're going to torture people.

361
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,400
They're going to pull women and children out.

362
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:48,200
They're going to pull grandmothers out.

363
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:50,080
And Stephen Miller is going to go berserk.

364
00:31:50,220 --> 00:31:52,180
And I was like, that's not going to happen.

365
00:31:52,420 --> 00:31:53,040
You're wrong.

366
00:31:53,140 --> 00:31:54,380
They're just going to get the criminals out.

367
00:31:54,460 --> 00:31:55,960
And this is a national security issue.

368
00:31:56,420 --> 00:31:58,740
And I reread those messages a couple of weeks ago.

369
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:01,100
And there's like dozens of messages between us.

370
00:32:01,140 --> 00:32:03,400
And I'm like, oh, my God, Mark Cuban was right.

371
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:07,080
Everything he said, I was like, Mark Cuban was right.

372
00:32:07,880 --> 00:32:11,560
And that's another thing that I feel immense guilt for.

373
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:21,360
And I haven't spoken about it because I just know I cultivated an audience of right wingers because there were certain things that I said that aligned with them at the time.

374
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:24,400
OK, I think most people again, you mentioned Biden and Obama.

375
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:28,520
I think a majority of people would say we should have some border security.

376
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:30,500
We should know who's coming in the country.

377
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:32,500
We should know where the children coming in the country are.

378
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:37,340
But that also evolved over time to where, no, we don't want any immigrants in here.

379
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:38,460
We're going to kick them all out.

380
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:44,020
We're going to deport people who have been here for decades and are good people with no criminal history.

381
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:52,700
And they're sitting here saying, you know, oh, and I've repeated these talking points like, oh, it's 100 percent the crime rate for immigrants because they're here illegally.

382
00:32:52,920 --> 00:33:05,460
But what I also realized is they love statistics, except when it's about demographics they don't like, like that men commit 92 percent of violent crimes, that they commit 98 percent of sexual assault, sexual violence.

383
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:09,480
And it was another moment where I'm like, this is really being used as a scapegoat.

384
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:13,420
And there is some merit to having sovereignty as a country.

385
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:30,180
But we should not be ripping out grandmothers and children and people who didn't do anything and shooting women in the face, moms in the face, because it was legally justifiable, because these are the same people who were cheering me on when I was running away from National Guard for the covid papers.

386
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:34,000
You know, so there's to me that's logically inconsistent.

387
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:37,020
And I know anyone listening to this is going to say, well, you didn't have a car.

388
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:38,340
You weren't putting their life at risk.

389
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:43,480
Well, if you take the left's logic, I was because covid and the pandemic and all of this stuff.

390
00:33:43,620 --> 00:33:45,900
So there is an argument for that as well.

391
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:46,600
I don't know.

392
00:33:46,660 --> 00:33:49,620
I just don't recognize what I was a part of.

393
00:33:50,060 --> 00:33:52,280
And I think in the moment it's a lot different.

394
00:33:52,280 --> 00:34:01,020
But looking back on things that I've said and things that I've helped usher in, like, I feel very dissociated and I'll read it and I'm like, did I really say that?

395
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:02,140
That was something I said.

396
00:34:02,500 --> 00:34:03,960
Like, this isn't photoshopped.

397
00:34:03,980 --> 00:34:04,920
I said that again.

398
00:34:05,140 --> 00:34:09,940
I've been very quiet on these issues because I don't want to come out and say now I know everything.

399
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:17,920
And now I have this, you know, flip flopped view when in reality, the only thing I'm doing is trying to understand offline.

400
00:34:18,620 --> 00:34:20,340
I'm trying to speak to people.

401
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:21,480
I'm trying to read.

402
00:34:21,620 --> 00:34:33,820
I'm trying to get information outside of tribes that I think has been helpful in developing a more human and reasonable understanding of all of these issues.

403
00:34:34,100 --> 00:34:38,600
It's interesting, too, because I feel like there's been so much fracturing in the movement.

404
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:43,760
Obviously, everyone's been following the drama with the right wing influencer world.

405
00:34:43,900 --> 00:34:47,440
And there's a lot of infighting and messiness and stuff.

406
00:34:47,699 --> 00:34:49,520
But it also does seem like a lot.

407
00:34:49,639 --> 00:34:58,380
I mean, part of why Candace Owens is so ascendant is speaking out against MAGA and calling on the hypocrisies, obviously very different hypocrisies.

408
00:34:58,480 --> 00:35:05,760
Like with her, it's mostly about Israel and what she whatever she thinks happened, the French Foreign Legion, you know, killing Charlie Kirk or whatever is the latest sort of thing.

409
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:10,020
But, you know, I do think that she has accurately called out some of this hypocrisy.

410
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:13,460
And it seems like she's been very ostracized from it.

411
00:35:13,520 --> 00:35:23,900
And I'm curious, kind of like what your experience has been like so far, like it is hard to be ostracized and like have people that that were very kind to you previously, like backed away or cut you off or treated you differently?

412
00:35:24,260 --> 00:35:24,720
Oh, yeah.

413
00:35:24,940 --> 00:35:28,580
And people can say whatever they want about someone like me or someone like Candace.

414
00:35:28,660 --> 00:35:32,040
But what they can't say is that we didn't see the underbelly of that beast.

415
00:35:32,560 --> 00:35:36,260
And people can demean me as just some conservative e-girl grifter.

416
00:35:36,460 --> 00:35:43,000
But that's really diminishing to the things that I saw and the places I was and the people I worked for and worked with.

417
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:50,360
And I did see how a lot of these things operate behind the scenes and what some of the true convictions of certain individuals were.

418
00:35:50,640 --> 00:35:57,440
It has been really hurtful because you also get to know these people as human beings, like I know their families and their kids and their parents.

419
00:35:57,700 --> 00:36:02,300
And they will say so loudly, we're speaking up because this is the right thing to do.

420
00:36:02,420 --> 00:36:08,660
And they won't speak up when someone like me, who they know is a good mom, they know that all of these things being said are not true.

421
00:36:08,820 --> 00:36:19,500
They're silent because they are very scared to be ostracized themselves because the party who is so vehemently against cancel culture, it's very easy to get canceled on the right.

422
00:36:19,740 --> 00:36:23,880
If you say, hey, I like some immigration, that's not kosher.

423
00:36:24,020 --> 00:36:26,400
You're not going to be taken seriously on the right at all.

424
00:36:26,480 --> 00:36:27,920
You're going to be ostracized.

425
00:36:28,460 --> 00:36:29,540
No party for you.

426
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:34,980
Even recently, Sarah Gonzalez, who I'm sure nobody knows, is a right-wing YouTuber.

427
00:36:35,300 --> 00:36:42,800
And she had a lot to say about my recent comments on the trans community and my apology to the trans community and the guilt that I felt.

428
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:46,600
And at one point as a gotcha, she says, everyone should unfollow her.

429
00:36:46,940 --> 00:36:54,040
Be careful who your heroes are, which by the way, if I was ever your hero, just posting online, you have deeper problems than me.

430
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:57,480
Not, you know, feeling bad that I said mean things about trans people.

431
00:36:57,680 --> 00:37:12,020
But she goes on to say, and by the way, just so you guys all know, she secretly would message me years ago when I would make jokes about repealing the 19th amendment and tell me that that wasn't funny and that they actually want to take rights away from women.

432
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:15,740
And I was like, is this like really the gotcha that I think women should vote?

433
00:37:15,860 --> 00:37:17,880
And I don't think your jokes are funny.

434
00:37:18,580 --> 00:37:19,940
So I don't know.

435
00:37:19,980 --> 00:37:23,660
And I look at all of this and I think many years ago, I would have been more hurt by it.

436
00:37:23,740 --> 00:37:28,360
But I just think they're all really sad and silly people.

437
00:37:28,940 --> 00:37:29,440
Well, it's hard.

438
00:37:29,540 --> 00:37:33,900
And I think also it's like you said, it's like, it's so hard to speak.

439
00:37:34,020 --> 00:37:38,940
I mean, I talked to another sort of former MAGA influencer who went the opposite way and then became very Democrat.

440
00:37:39,100 --> 00:37:49,840
And I think sometimes like you feel so ostracized that you want to just like rush to like the other team or whatever, and they want to use you too, you know, and then you get sort of disenchanted with this whole system.

441
00:37:50,740 --> 00:37:50,840
Yeah.

442
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:52,800
There's so many issues with the Democrat party.

443
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:54,720
I also don't think they're radical enough.

444
00:37:55,180 --> 00:38:06,040
If I'm being honest, like they're not radical enough for me to join, because me, I'm like, I'm sitting here listening to the most powerful people in the world complain about like socialism and healthcare and handouts.

445
00:38:06,180 --> 00:38:10,320
And the handouts in question is like my mom going to the hospital when she has a heart attack.

446
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:14,840
And the Democrats really have not stepped up to the plate on the real issues at hand.

447
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:20,060
They're also being very trivial about the issues that are center focus on their platforms.

448
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:27,560
So I'm not running into the arms of everyone, but I will say it was, it was, I don't want to cry.

449
00:38:27,740 --> 00:38:37,500
But when I put out that statement, my apology to the people that I had hurt within the trans community, there was a certain individual who did not like that very much.

450
00:38:37,700 --> 00:38:44,520
And now there are, you know, 122,000 posts on the subject, attacking me and threatening my family.

451
00:38:44,920 --> 00:38:51,860
And I wanted to cry because there were people on the left and within the trans community that were then sticking up for me.

452
00:38:51,980 --> 00:38:55,280
And they didn't know me that, and I'm not asking for them to do that.

453
00:38:55,360 --> 00:39:02,240
And I really said quite mean things, but like that was to me, like very, that was very kind.

454
00:39:02,780 --> 00:39:19,680
So, I mean, I saw, yeah, Elon Musk is trying to like use the fact that you said like, wow, I feel really bad for, you know, my role in this and my views evolved is trying to use that as some like, you know, excuse to take the child that you have together away and fight for full custody or something obscene, which is disgusting.

455
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:26,140
And also saying that you're trying to like trans your child or something, which is just absurd because you're such a loving mother.

456
00:39:26,740 --> 00:39:47,320
Well, I can't comment that on that in particular, you know, there's, there's a lot of people who are now sending a lot of threats and it's put a real target on my back that people who do not have a third grade reading comprehension level or skillset understand what I was saying in that post.

457
00:39:47,580 --> 00:39:55,280
And I hope that more people feel some sort of courage to have more nuanced opinions and admit when they were wrong.

458
00:39:55,420 --> 00:40:00,540
Like, it's not fun for me to say, hey, I was wrong and a horrible human being.

459
00:40:00,540 --> 00:40:02,460
And I said a lot of mean things.

460
00:40:02,660 --> 00:40:10,860
This isn't fun for me to do and say, I was actually really stupid and really privileged and kind of an asshole.

461
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:16,660
Like that's not, I don't wake up saying like, today I'm going to disparage myself.

462
00:40:17,420 --> 00:40:19,960
Like that's not fun for my next grift.

463
00:40:20,100 --> 00:40:23,660
I will call myself a bumbling, nasty idiot.

464
00:40:23,860 --> 00:40:28,340
And I think that people who really know me and my support network, they know those things are true.

465
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:30,940
And I've said these things privately that I said publicly.

466
00:40:31,200 --> 00:40:36,400
And when I say them privately with normal people, it's met with a normal reaction.

467
00:40:36,880 --> 00:40:52,980
And there there's this platform, Twitter, is being very manipulated for an agenda, for certain rhetorics that appease a certain audience so that people feel that normal opinions are more abnormal than they really are.

468
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:56,060
That hits at you when there's that many people who dislike you.

469
00:40:56,140 --> 00:40:57,380
You're like, am I wrong?

470
00:40:58,120 --> 00:41:00,380
And that's just not the case.

471
00:41:00,460 --> 00:41:03,960
And people need to be very cognizant of the fact that they're being manipulated.

472
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:08,920
And if the internet was blown up tomorrow, I don't think they would feel this way.

473
00:41:09,340 --> 00:41:09,440
Yeah.

474
00:41:09,580 --> 00:41:24,140
I think algorithmic feeds, like, I mean, it's so interesting because algorithmic feeds also came into fruition during Trump 1.0. I think Twitter got theirs in 2016 or 2017, but that is when algorithmic feeds started to basically reshape social media.

475
00:41:24,360 --> 00:41:36,440
And I think it changed the culture of so many of these platforms, especially when you have someone at the helm of like X or Twitter or whatever, or any of these that are able to manipulate the algorithm in certain ways and push certain views.

476
00:41:36,640 --> 00:41:40,160
And also we know that a lot of these algorithms reward outrage and hate.

477
00:41:40,300 --> 00:41:43,820
And right-wingers have always performed better in engagement-based algorithms.

478
00:41:44,080 --> 00:41:53,020
And so I think, yeah, it's like so easy to get sucked in and think that everybody believes this or that these issues are more widespread and popular than they really are.

479
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:53,540
Yeah.

480
00:41:53,600 --> 00:41:54,500
And that's dangerous.

481
00:41:54,740 --> 00:41:59,220
And for the same reason that we have to regulate Grok, this is why we have to regulate these platforms.

482
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:08,040
And particularly when the owner of the platform is indeed acting as an editor, in no uncertain terms, they are acting as an editor of that platform.

483
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:10,300
They don't deserve Section 230 protections.

484
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:15,400
And people will call me, you know, that I'm turning because I'm scorned, but do the research.

485
00:42:15,580 --> 00:42:17,280
I have always spoken about these issues.

486
00:42:17,420 --> 00:42:22,080
I've always spoken about removing Section 230 protections from big tech platforms.

487
00:42:22,300 --> 00:42:27,860
So I did change as much as people think they also changed a lot.

488
00:42:28,040 --> 00:42:29,600
Well, I think here's the thing.

489
00:42:29,860 --> 00:42:31,520
We don't want to dismantle Section 230.

490
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:34,800
That allows us to have speech on the internet, in my opinion.

491
00:42:35,100 --> 00:42:36,660
And we have to protect free speech.

492
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:38,940
If we don't protect free speech, like what are we even doing?

493
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:41,640
Like we have no chance at resisting authoritarianism.

494
00:42:42,100 --> 00:42:48,280
But I completely agree that Elon Musk has sailed through with no tech regulation, like no protections.

495
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:59,140
And all of the tech regulation currently is focused on censoring users and not targeting the CEOs of these companies, not targeting their business models, not holding actually Elon Musk accountable.

496
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:03,060
This is why Elon Musk himself supports the Kids Online Safety Act.

497
00:43:03,340 --> 00:43:04,120
Like exactly.

498
00:43:04,520 --> 00:43:07,340
It doesn't do anything to affect him or his business model.

499
00:43:07,480 --> 00:43:08,780
It affects users.

500
00:43:09,080 --> 00:43:23,640
And that's why when I say, you know, remove Section 230 from big tech, because even they are so out of control and their standards are so, like you said, misapplied to individual users, as opposed to the levers of power.

501
00:43:23,960 --> 00:43:34,040
Even if you take Apple, for example, which I know doesn't really apply to Section 230, but big tech more generally, they are going through each one of your photos to see if they're CSAM.

502
00:43:34,240 --> 00:43:38,840
Yet they did not remove X from the app store when Grok was producing CSAM.

503
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:40,840
And this was a very well-known problem.

504
00:43:41,300 --> 00:43:42,120
Neither did Google.

505
00:43:42,260 --> 00:43:48,820
They didn't even put out a statement on it saying, hey, buddy, could you please make the robot stop making CSAM?

506
00:43:48,820 --> 00:43:50,880
But they're going to go through every one of your photos.

507
00:43:51,340 --> 00:43:52,520
You might get stopped at the airport.

508
00:43:52,700 --> 00:44:02,540
I'm so scared that because I saved some of these images from Grok, that I'm going to end up stopped at TSA next time I go because Apple's gone through my camera roll and thinks I'm a pervert.

509
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:04,300
But it's so misapplied.

510
00:44:04,460 --> 00:44:10,880
And there's really no policing within the tech community itself, within the tech billionaires themselves.

511
00:44:11,120 --> 00:44:23,480
And they very much protect each other and have kind of co-opted populism and issues that people are really desperate about, such as free speech, as a guise to usher in their own desires.

512
00:44:24,140 --> 00:44:28,460
I mean, Elon Musk constantly posts about free speech, like literally while he's banning journalists from the app.

513
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:30,100
Still, Travis Brown remains banned.

514
00:44:30,160 --> 00:44:31,220
A bunch of journalists remain banned.

515
00:44:31,300 --> 00:44:32,160
It's absolutely ridiculous.

516
00:44:32,400 --> 00:44:32,720
But yeah.

517
00:44:32,900 --> 00:44:41,040
And I mean, I don't know, in terms of Section 230 reform, I don't trust the government to do that because the government is so in bed with these evil corporations that I don't trust.

518
00:44:41,260 --> 00:44:44,140
Like, would I personally write Section 230 a little bit differently?

519
00:44:44,460 --> 00:44:50,020
Maybe, yeah, if I had the opportunity, but I don't trust our current government to do that in a way that would actually target these tech.

520
00:44:50,120 --> 00:45:02,560
And I guess I want to see them pass some sort of laws that would actually target these companies' business models before I trust them to, like, I guess, like, reform this, like, landmark law that protects so much speech online.

521
00:45:02,960 --> 00:45:05,380
We're going to have to go back to Buckley v.

522
00:45:05,620 --> 00:45:05,940
Valeo.

523
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:09,680
You know, they have now said that money is speech.

524
00:45:09,900 --> 00:45:16,640
So there is a very elite percentage of people who technically, under the law, have more speech than we do, an infinite amount.

525
00:45:16,820 --> 00:45:18,000
And that is very dangerous.

526
00:45:18,140 --> 00:45:21,740
And I think that's probably a good place for people to refocus energy.

527
00:45:22,260 --> 00:45:23,000
Yeah, I know.

528
00:45:23,060 --> 00:45:25,520
Well, I have a whole miniseries coming on Section 230.

